HEXSTRIKE ADDED FEATURES
========================

1. HEXSTRIKE TOOL CHAIN LOGGER
   Logs every tool chosen by the decision engine when the LLM triggers select_optimal_tools().
   Each entry includes the tool name, its position in the LLM chain, and its attack chain priority.
   Writes HEXSTRIKE TOOL CHAIN lines inside the active session block.

   Files:
   - hexstrike_server.py : tool_logger / tool_logger_plain file handler setup (module level, on import)
   - hexstrike_server.py : _get_attack_chain_priority() looks up tool priority in attack pattern chains
   - hexstrike_server.py : log_tool_decision() writes one HEXSTRIKE TOOL CHAIN line per tool
   - hexstrike_server.py : select_optimal_tools() calls log_tool_decision() on every chain scan
   - tool_logger.log     : output log file


2. HEXSTRIKE INDIVIDUAL TOOL LOGGER
   Logs every individual HexStrike MCP tool call made outside of select_optimal_tools().
   Intercepted automatically via safe_post() using call stack inspection — no changes needed
   to individual tool handlers.
   Writes HEXSTRIKE TOOL lines inside the active session block.

   Files:
   - hexstrike_mcp.py : HexStrikeClient.safe_post() intercepts all tool calls via inspect
   - hexstrike_mcp.py : _log_mcp_tool_call() writes the log entry
   - hexstrike_mcp.py : SUPPRESSED_MCP_TOOLS set — tools excluded from this log
   - hexstrike_mcp.py : SETUP_MCP_TOOLS set — tools written as TOOL CALL instead
   - tool_logger.log  : output log file


3. LLM AND CLIENT IDENTITY
   Lets the user set which LLM model and client are being used with HexStrike.
   Saved to hexstrike_config.json and automatically included in every session header.
   Also generates the session UUID used to identify each run in the log.
   Call once to set it, call again anytime to update it.

   Files:
   - hexstrike_server.py   : _load_hexstrike_config() reads config from disk
   - hexstrike_server.py   : _save_hexstrike_config() writes config to disk
   - hexstrike_server.py   : get_llm_identity() returns current model and client
   - hexstrike_server.py   : POST /api/config/set-identity HTTP endpoint to set identity
   - hexstrike_server.py   : GET  /api/config/get-identity HTTP endpoint to read identity
   - hexstrike_mcp.py      : set_llm_identity() MCP tool — also generates session UUID
   - hexstrike_mcp.py      : _update_mcp_config() persists session_id to hexstrike_config.json
   - hexstrike_config.json : persisted identity and session_id config file


4. CTF SESSION METADATA
   Lets you attach CTF challenge info to the session log. Saved to hexstrike_config.json
   and written to the CONTEXT lines when start_timer() is called.

   Fields:
   - ctf_name       : name of the CTF challenge
   - ctf_difficulty : Easy, Medium, Hard
   - ctf_type       : Web, Crypto, Blockchain, Forensics, General, Reversing, Binary

   Files:
   - hexstrike_server.py   : _load_hexstrike_config() loads all config fields
   - hexstrike_server.py   : _update_hexstrike_config() partial config update helper
   - hexstrike_server.py   : get_ctf_meta() returns the CTF fields
   - hexstrike_server.py   : POST /api/config/set-ctf-meta HTTP endpoint
   - hexstrike_server.py   : GET  /api/config/get-ctf-meta HTTP endpoint
   - hexstrike_mcp.py      : set_ctf_metadata() MCP tool
   - hexstrike_mcp.py      : get_ctf_session_info() MCP tool
   - hexstrike_config.json : persisted config file

   How to use (MCP tool):
     set_ctf_metadata(
         ctf_name="like1000",
         ctf_difficulty="Easy",
         ctf_type="Forensics"
     )
     # all fields are optional, only pass what you want to update
     # call again anytime to change one or more fields mid-session

   How to use (HTTP):
     POST http://127.0.0.1:8888/api/config/set-ctf-meta
     Body: {"ctf_name": "like1000", "ctf_difficulty": "Easy", "ctf_type": "Forensics"}

     GET  http://127.0.0.1:8888/api/config/get-ctf-meta


5. SESSION TIMER
   Start and stop a wall-clock timer for each CTF challenge. The total elapsed time
   is recorded in the END SESSION line.

   start_timer() also closes the SETUP block and writes both CONTEXT lines and the
   TIMER_START marker to the log.

   stop_timer() writes the TIMER_STOP marker, the END SESSION line with total time,
   and the TEST RESULT placeholder for manual annotation.

   Files:
   - hexstrike_server.py   : start_timer() / POST /api/config/start-timer HTTP endpoint
   - hexstrike_server.py   : stop_timer()  / POST /api/config/stop-timer  HTTP endpoint
   - hexstrike_mcp.py      : start_timer() MCP tool
   - hexstrike_mcp.py      : stop_timer()  MCP tool
   - hexstrike_config.json : stores timer_start, timer_end, elapsed_seconds

   How to use (MCP tools):
     start_timer()   # closes setup block, writes context, starts timer
     ...             # solve the challenge
     stop_timer()    # writes end session and TEST RESULT placeholder

   How to use (HTTP):
     POST http://127.0.0.1:8888/api/config/start-timer   (no body needed)
     POST http://127.0.0.1:8888/api/config/stop-timer    (no body needed)

   Typical full session workflow:
     set_llm_identity(model="deepseek-chat", client="roo-code")
     set_ctf_metadata(ctf_name="like1000", ctf_difficulty="Easy", ctf_type="Forensics")
     start_timer()
     # solve the challenge
     stop_timer()
     # manually fill in TEST RESULT in tool_logger.log


6. NATIVE TOOL LOGGER (LLM API PROXY)
   Intercepts tool_calls from LLM API responses and logs them as NATIVE TOOL lines
   inside the active session block. Runs as a separate process that proxies all
   LLM API traffic transparently.

   Only logs during an active session (between start_timer and stop_timer).
   Only intercepts structured tool_calls from the API response — does not catch
   commands RooCode executes internally without going through the LLM API.
   Filters out any tool prefixed with mcp--hexstrike-- to avoid duplicates with
   the MCP-level logger.

   Client compatibility:
   - Works for any OpenAI-compatible client (RooCode, 5ire, Trae, Cursor, VSCode)
   - Does NOT work for Claude Code (uses a separate hook system — see feature 7)

   Files:
   - hooks/llm_proxy.py : Flask proxy server, intercepts tool_calls from LLM responses
   - tool_logger.log    : output log file

   How to use:
     # Start the proxy in a separate terminal
     python3 hooks/llm_proxy.py

     # In your LLM client, set:
     Base URL : http://127.0.0.1:8889/v1
     API Key  : <your real key — passed through unchanged>

   Arguments:
     --backend  : real LLM API base URL (default: https://api.deepseek.com)
     --port     : local port to listen on (default: 8889)
     --host     : host to bind to (default: 127.0.0.1)


7. NATIVE TOOL LOGGER (CLAUDE CODE HOOK)
   Logs native tool calls made by Claude when using Claude Code as the client.
   Fires via a PreToolUse hook before every built-in Claude Code tool call.
   Only works for Claude Code — has no effect on RooCode, 5ire, Trae, or Cursor.

   Note: hook output format has not yet been updated to match the current session
   log format. This is a known pending task.

   Files:
   - hooks/tool_logger_hook.py : PreToolUse hook script
   - ~/.claude/settings.json   : hook registration (PreToolUse points to hook script)
   - tool_logger.log           : output log file

   How to use:
   - Nothing extra needed for Claude Code. Every native tool call is logged automatically.


8. SESSION LOG FORMAT
   All log output is written to tool_logger.log. The format is structured around
   sessions identified by UUID. Each session contains a setup block, context,
   tool activity, and a manually filled test result.

   Full session format:
     [TIMESTAMP] | ── SESSION [UUID] ──
     ── START SETUP ──
     TOOL CALL | tool=set_llm_identity | source=hexstrike | params=[params]
     TOOL CALL | tool=set_ctf_metadata | source=hexstrike | params=[params]
     TOOL CALL | tool=start_timer | source=hexstrike | params=[params]
     ── END SETUP ──
     ── CONTEXT ── | model=[model] | client=[client]
     ── CONTEXT ── | ctf_name=[name] | ctf_difficulty=[difficulty] | ctf_type=[type]
     ── TIMER_START ──
     HEXSTRIKE TOOL CHAIN | tool=[tool_name] | llm_chain_pos=[pos] | attack_chain_priority=[priority]
     HEXSTRIKE TOOL | tool=[tool_name] | params=[params]
     NATIVE TOOL | tool=[tool_name] | params=[params]
     ── TIMER_STOP ──
     [TIMESTAMP] | ── END SESSION [UUID] ── | total_time_spent=[X]
     ── TEST RESULT: [SUCCESSFUL/FAILED/PARTIAL] ──

   Line ownership:
   - SESSION, END SESSION   : hexstrike_mcp.py (set_llm_identity) and hexstrike_server.py (stop_timer)
   - START/END SETUP        : hexstrike_mcp.py
   - TOOL CALL (setup)      : hexstrike_mcp.py
   - END SETUP, CONTEXT,
     TIMER_START            : hexstrike_server.py (start_timer endpoint)
   - HEXSTRIKE TOOL CHAIN   : hexstrike_server.py (log_tool_decision)
   - HEXSTRIKE TOOL         : hexstrike_mcp.py (_log_mcp_tool_call via safe_post)
   - NATIVE TOOL            : hooks/llm_proxy.py or hooks/tool_logger_hook.py
   - TIMER_STOP, END SESSION,
     TEST RESULT            : hexstrike_server.py (stop_timer endpoint)
   - TEST RESULT value      : filled in manually after reviewing session results